    "# -------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "# FASE 1 - Análisis gráfico exhaustivo (Actividad 3: Arriendos Bogotá)\n",
    "# Pega esto en una celda del Jupyter Notebook y ejecútalo.\n",
    "# -------------------------------------------------------\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ruta del CSV (ajusta si tu archivo tiene otro nombre o ruta)\n",
    "path = \"data/base_arriendos.csv\"\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(path)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Normalizar columnas\n",
    "df.columns = [c.strip() for c in df.columns]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Inspección rápida\n",
    "print(\"Dimensiones:\", df.shape)\n",
    "print(\"Columnas:\", df.columns.tolist())\n",
    "display(df.head())\n",
    "\n",
    "# Intento automático de detectar columnas relevantes (si no coinciden, cambia las variables manualmente)\n",
    "possible_price_cols = [c for c in df.columns if 'preci' in c.lower() or 'valor' in c.lower() or 'arriendo' in c.lower() or 'canon' in c.lower() or 'rent' in c.lower()]\n",
    "possible_area_cols = [c for c in df.columns if 'area' in c.lower() or 'm2' in c.lower() or 'metros' in c.lower() or 'superficie' in c.lower()]\n",
    "possible_stratum_cols = [c for c in df.columns if 'estrato' in c.lower() or c.lower().strip()=='estr']\n",
    "possible_zone_cols = [c for c in df.columns if 'barrio' in c.lower() or 'zona' in c.lower() or 'comuna' in c.lower() or 'localidad' in c.lower()]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Candidatas precio:\", possible_price_cols)\n",
    "print(\"Candidatas area:\", possible_area_cols)\n",
    "print(\"Candidatas estrato:\", possible_stratum_cols)\n",
    "print(\"Candidatas barrio/zona:\", possible_zone_cols)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Si el auto-detección falla, pon el nombre exacto aquí:\n",
    "price_col = possible_price_cols[0] if possible_price_cols else \"precio\"\n",
    "area_col = possible_area_cols[0] if possible_area_cols else None\n",
    "stratum_col = possible_stratum_cols[0] if possible_stratum_cols else None\n",
    "zone_col = possible_zone_cols[0] if possible_zone_cols else None\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Usando -> precio: {price_col}, area: {area_col}, estrato: {stratum_col}, zona: {zone_col}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Convertir a numérico (sobreescribe con NaN cuando no convertible)\n",
    "df[price_col] = pd.to_numeric(df[price_col], errors='coerce')\n",
    "if area_col:\n",
    "    df[area_col] = pd.to_numeric(df[area_col], errors='coerce')\n",
    "if stratum_col:\n",
    "    df[stratum_col] = pd.to_numeric(df[stratum_col], errors='coerce').astype('Int64', errors='ignore')\n",
    "if zone_col:\n",
    "    df[zone_col] = df[zone_col].astype(str)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Carpeta de salida\n",
    "out_dir = Path(\"arriendos_outputs\")\n",
    "out_dir.mkdir(exist_ok=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1) Histograma precio (ver distribución, sesgos y outliers)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(9,4))\n",
    "plt.hist(df[price_col].dropna(), bins=60)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Histograma - Precio de arriendo\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Precio\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Frecuencia\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(out_dir/\"hist_precio.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2) Boxplot precio por estrato (si existe)\n",
    "if stratum_col:\n",
    "    groups = df[[stratum_col, price_col]].dropna()\n",
    "    orden = sorted(groups[stratum_col].dropna().unique())\n",
    "    data = [groups[groups[stratum_col]==e][price_col].values for e in orden]\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(10,5))\n",
    "    plt.boxplot(data, labels=orden, showfliers=False)\n",
    "    plt.title(\"Boxplot Precio por Estrato (sin outliers visualizados)\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Estrato\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Precio\")\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.savefig(out_dir/\"box_precio_estrato.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"No se detectó columna de estrato. Si existe, asigna su nombre manualmente a stratum_col.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 3) Boxplot por zona (top 12 zonas por cantidad)\n",
    "if zone_col:\n",
    "    top_zonas = df[zone_col].value_counts().nlargest(12).index.tolist()\n",
    "    data_zone = [df[df[zone_col]==z][price_col].dropna().values for z in top_zonas]\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))\n",
    "    plt.boxplot(data_zone, labels=top_zonas, showfliers=False)\n",
    "    plt.title(\"Boxplot Precio por Zona (Top 12 por cantidad)\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Zona / Barrio\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Precio\")\n",
    "    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.savefig(out_dir/\"box_precio_zona_top12.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"No se detectó columna de zona/barrio. Si existe, asigna su nombre manualmente a zone_col.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 4) Scatter Precio vs Área (si área disponible)\n",
    "if area_col:\n",
    "    samp = df[[area_col, price_col]].dropna()\n",
    "    if len(samp) > 5000:\n",
    "        samp = samp.sample(5000, random_state=42)\n",
    "    plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))\n",
    "    plt.scatter(samp[area_col], samp[price_col], s=8, alpha=0.5)\n",
    "    plt.title(\"Scatter: Precio vs Área\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel(\"Área\")\n",
    "    plt.ylabel(\"Precio\")\n",
    "    plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "    plt.savefig(out_dir/\"scatter_precio_area.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"No se detectó columna de área. Si existe, asigna su nombre manualmente a area_col.\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 5) Correlación entre variables numéricas (precio, área, estrato si numérico)\n",
    "num_cols = [price_col]\n",
    "if area_col:\n",
    "    num_cols.append(area_col)\n",
    "if stratum_col:\n",
    "    num_cols.append(stratum_col)\n",
    "corr = df[num_cols].dropna().corr()\n",
    "print(\"\\nMatriz de correlación (numéricas):\")\n",
    "display(corr)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(4,3))\n",
    "plt.imshow(corr, cmap='viridis', aspect='auto')\n",
    "plt.colorbar()\n",
    "plt.xticks(range(len(num_cols)), num_cols, rotation=45)\n",
    "plt.yticks(range(len(num_cols)), num_cols)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Matriz de Correlación (numérica)\")\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.savefig(out_dir/\"corr_matrix.png\", dpi=150)\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# 6) Resumen por estrato y por zona (mediana, promedio, count)\n",
    "if stratum_col:\n",
    "    summary_e = df.groupby(stratum_col)[price_col].agg(['count','median','mean','std']).reset_index().sort_values('median', ascending=False)\n",
    "    summary_e.to_csv(out_dir/\"summary_estrato.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "    print(\"Resumen por estrato guardado:\", out_dir/\"summary_estrato.csv\")\n",
    "    display(summary_e.head(10))\n",
    "if zone_col:\n",
    "    summary_z = df.groupby(zone_col)[price_col].agg(['count','median','mean','std']).reset_index().sort_values('count', ascending=False)\n",
    "    summary_z.to_csv(out_dir/\"summary_zona_top.csv\", index=False)\n",
    "    print(\"Resumen por zona guardado:\", out_dir/\"summary_zona_top.csv\")\n",
    "    display(summary_z.head(10))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"\\nFase 1 completada: revisa la carpeta 'arriendos_outputs' para los PNGs y CSVs generados.\")\n"
   ]

    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "# 1️⃣ Cargar base\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "df = pd.read_csv(\"data/base_arriendos.csv\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Renombrar columnas clave para facilitar el análisis\n",
    "df = df.rename(columns={\n",
    "    \"Rent Price\": \"precio\",\n",
    "    \"Area (sqm)\": \"area\"\n",
    "})\n",
    "\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "# 2️⃣ Limpieza básica de valores nulos y sentido común\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "df_limpio = df[\n",
    "    (df[\"precio\"].notna()) & (df[\"precio\"] > 0) &\n",
    "    (df[\"area\"].notna()) & (df[\"area\"] >= 10)\n",
    "].copy()\n",
    "\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "# 3️⃣ Función para eliminar outliers usando IQR\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "def filtrar_outliers_iqr(df, columna):\n",
    "    Q1 = df[columna].quantile(0.25)\n",
    "    Q3 = df[columna].quantile(0.75)\n",
    "    IQR = Q3 - Q1\n",
    "    lower = Q1 - 1.5 * IQR\n",
    "    upper = Q3 + 1.5 * IQR\n",
    "    return df[(df[columna] >= lower) & (df[columna] <= upper)]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Aplicar filtrado por IQR\n",
    "df_limpio = filtrar_outliers_iqr(df_limpio, \"precio\")\n",
    "df_limpio = filtrar_outliers_iqr(df_limpio, \"area\")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Registros originales: {len(df):,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Registros después de limpieza: {len(df_limpio):,}\")\n",
    "print(df_limpio[[\"area\",\"precio\"]].describe())\n",
    "\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "# 4️⃣ Transformación logarítmica para visualización\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "df_limpio[\"precio_log\"] = np.log1p(df_limpio[\"precio\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "# 5️⃣ Scatter plot (Precio vs Área)\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))\n",
    "sns.scatterplot(data=df_limpio, x=\"area\", y=\"precio\", alpha=0.5)\n",
    "plt.title(\"Relación entre Área y Precio (sin outliers)\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Área (m²)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Precio (COP)\")\n",
    "plt.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "# 6️⃣ Scatter logarítmico (para ver tendencia)\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8,6))\n",
    "sns.scatterplot(data=df_limpio, x=\"area\", y=\"precio_log\", alpha=0.5, color=\"darkgreen\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Relación logarítmica entre Área y Precio\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Área (m²)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Log(Precio + 1)\")\n",
    "plt.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "# 7️⃣ Histograma de precios\n",
    "# ======================================================\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8,5))\n",
    "sns.histplot(df_limpio[\"precio\"], bins=40, kde=True, color=\"royalblue\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Distribución del Precio de Arriendo (sin outliers)\")\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"Precio (millones de COP)\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"Frecuencia\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Formato del eje X en millones\n",
    "ticks = np.arange(0, df_limpio[\"precio\"].max() + 2_000_000, 2_000_000)\n",
    "labels = [f\"{int(x/1_000_000)}M\" for x in ticks]\n",
    "plt.xticks(ticks, labels)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n"
   ]
